{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "a1b2c3d4-e5f6-7890-abcd-ef1234567890",
    "name": "Amigo Enterprises API",
    "description": "ESP Servicing & Invoicing ERP — full backend API collection.\n\n## Setup\n1. Import this collection and an environment file (Local, Render, or Vercel).\n2. Set `baseUrl`, `email`, `password`, and `cronSecret` to match your deployment.\n   - `email` / `password` must match the super-admin from `npm run seed` (SEED_SUPERADMIN_* env vars).\n   - `cronSecret` must match the `CRON_SECRET` env var on the server.\n3. Select your environment (e.g. **Render** for `https://YOUR-SERVICE.onrender.com`).\n4. Run **Auth → Login** first (session cookie is stored automatically).\n5. Use other requests — IDs are auto-saved from list/create responses where possible.\n\n## Auth\nSession-based (`connect.sid` cookie). Postman stores cookies after Login. Enable cookies in Postman settings for HTTPS (Render/Vercel).\n\n## RBAC (roles)\n- **super_admin / admin:** Users, Verification, Invoice finalize/cancel/payments/delete, AMC create/update/delete, Org Settings PUT.\n- **employee:** Read-mostly access; admin-only routes return 403.\n\n## OTP flows\nFor **Create User** and **Finalize Invoice** when SMTP OTP is enabled:\n1. Verification → OTP Status\n2. Verification → Request OTP\n3. Verification → Verify OTP\n4. Call create/finalize with `verificationId` in body.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
